        <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Which is better for beginners: Canva or Adobe Express?</h3>
    <p>Canva is more beginner-friendly with its intuitive drag-and-drop interface and massive template library. Adobe Express is also accessible but assumes some design knowledge. Canva's shorter learning curve makes it the better choice for complete beginners.</p>
    <h3>Can Adobe Express replace Canva for social media design?</h3>
    <p>Adobe Express can create social media content but has fewer templates and a smaller community. Canva's platform-specific templates, scheduling integrations, and larger asset library make it the stronger choice for dedicated social media content creation.</p>
    <h3>Which tool has better AI features for design?</h3>
    <p>Adobe Express integrates Adobe Firefly, which generates commercially-safe images trained on licensed content. Canva's Magic Studio offers a wider range of AI tools including text-to-image, image expansion, and object removal, but its copyright stance is less clear for commercial use.</p>
    <h3>Is Canva or Adobe Express more affordable for teams?</h3>
    <p>Canva Pro costs $13/month for up to 5 team members, making it excellent value for small teams. Adobe Express Premium costs $10/month for one user. For larger teams, Canva's per-seat pricing for up to 5 users is more cost-effective.</p>
